# 5. 在りし日の思い出

Emu: “Then, let's go to the next city!”
Emu: Yeah...! I've got this line down!
Emu: And the next part's the final scene. Let's see...
Emu: “And they made shows together forever after”...
Emu: They made shows together... Forever after...
Tsukasa: Okay, it seems we're all on the same page!
Tsukasa: Wonderlands×Showtime shall continue operations!
Emu: (I remember feeling so happy that time...)
Emu: (My heart was full of joy and excitement about how we were going to put on lots and lots of shows together...)
Emu: (And we really did put on a lot...)
Emu: (Our shows were so amazingly spectacular that I had a ton of fun just practicing them.)
Emu: (And I wished that things would never change.)
Emu: (No...)
Emu: (I've made my decision.)
Emu: (If I don't stay strong, the others are gonna start to worry.)
Emu: (I have to keep smiling.)
Hinata's Voice: Emu, do you have a minute?
Emu: Oh, Sis...! Yeah, come in!
Hinata: I'm sorry to bother you so suddenly. I wanted to have some hot chocolate and ended up making a little too much. Would you like some as well, Emu?
Emu: Oh... Yeah!
Emu: Wait, but I just brushed my teeth! Will it be okay if I brush them again after?!
Hinata: Hehe. Yes, I'd say that's fine.
Emu: Then, I'll have some! Bottoms up!
Emu: Hehe... It's so warm and sweet...
Emu: My chest is feeling all fuzzy wuzzy...
Hinata: ...
Hinata: Is something wrong, Emu...?
Emu: What?
Hinata: You looked a little unhappy there for a second.
Emu: H-Huh? I did? No, I'm...
Emu: ...
Emu: You're right... I don't feel completely happy.
Emu: Can we talk for a bit, Sis?
Hinata: Yes, I'm here to listen.
Hinata: I see... And they'll be freelancing from here on out...
Emu: Yeah...
Hinata: Are you sure about your decision, Emu...? Don't you want to go with them?
Emu: I'm sure...
Emu: Because I'm never going to forget what we did.
Emu: Seeing all those shows with Grandpa...
Little Emu: Grr... Grandpa, I can't see. It's too dark...
Rakunosuke: Heh heh heh. Just another second, dear. Ah, excellent...!
Rakunosuke: I'll remove your blindfold in...! Three, two, one...
Little Emu: Wah! It's so bright!
Little Emu: Huh...?
Little Emu: Grandpa? Where are we?
Rakunosuke: Hehe. This is nowhere in particular, but it can also be anywhere you like!
Little Emu: Nowhere, but anywhere...?
Rakunosuke: Yes, that's right!
Rakunosuke: Ah, however... Today, it seems that it's going to be a magical forest. Take a look at the stage.
Cast Member: Welcome to the Wonder Stage, everyone!
Little Emu: The Wonder Stage...?
Cast Member: Today's showing of “Teddy In The Magical Forest” will begin in ten minutes!
Little Emu: Oh wow...! Lots of people just came in!
Rakunosuke: Ah, I should probably lower my head a bit to make sure the little ones can see.
Rakunosuke: Now, Emu, take another look at the stage.
Rakunosuke: What you're about to experience is going to feel like a wonderful dream!
Little Emu: Wow...!!!
Teddy Bear: “*Sigh* Why does everyone disappear whenever I try to go play in the forest? Are they afraid of how I look?”
Teddy Bear: “I know I seem scary, but I still want to become friends with them...”
Teddy Bear: “Oh where, oh where could all the forest critters have gone?”
Little Emu: Over there!
Children: There!
Rakunosuke: Yes, they're over there! Listen to my granddaughter!
Lala the Rabbit: “I'm too afraid! Us rabbits can't walk around the forest knowing that such a big, scary bear is lurking!”
Little Emu: No, don't be afraid! He's a nice bear!
Vivi the Squirrel: “Hey, what if that bear isn't as scary as we thought? He looks a little mean, but he could be nice.”
Little Emu: He is! He wants to be friends with all of you!
Vivi the Squirrel: “Look...! The bear's keeping that tree from falling! He prevented our homes from being crushed!”
Forest Animals: “We gotta help him! Let's go, everyone!”
Little Emu: ...!!! Grandpa, Mr. Bear's about to make some new friends!
Rakunosuke: *Sob* I'm so happy for him...!
Little Emu: Huh...? Grandpa, are you crying? Why?
Rakunosuke: How can I not cry?! I'm just so happy that our bear finally has friends to play with!
Rakunosuke: Still, this is supposed to be a happy ending... As such, I should be smiling.
Cast Member: “Let's all finish by singing together!”
Little Emu & Rakunosuke: Yeah!!!
Little Emu: Hehe...♪ I didn't know shows were so much fun, Grandpa!
Rakunosuke: They really are, aren't they?!
Rakunosuke: This stage has the power to take you to a different world for every show.
Rakunosuke: You could be in the jungle, on top of the clouds, in prehistoric times or even in outer space...
Rakunosuke: It's a wonderland that can take you anywhere at all.
Little Emu: A wonderland...?
Rakunosuke: If you ever want to smile, Emu, you should visit this stage. I guarantee that it'll take you somewhere fantastic.
Rakunosuke: And once what you've seen here has made you smile, you should take a look at the world around you...
Rakunosuke: Unfortunately, unlike what you see on stage, it's not all full of smiles and happiness.
Rakunosuke: But I'm sure what you witness will become the fuel that drives you.
Little Emu: Okay!!!
Emu: Grandpa was right... The Wonder Stage made me smile so many times after that.
Emu: And seeing everyone else smile there makes me really happy too...
Emu: So, I want to protect them both.
Emu: The Wonder Stage and Phoenix Wonderland that Grandpa left to us.
Hinata: Emu...
Emu: It's really sad that I won't be able to do shows with the others like I used to... But I'm okay with that.
Emu: I think we'll be able to smile while we say goodbye to each other.
Emu: Even though they won't be members of the Wonder Stage cast anymore.
Emu: Even though we won't be doing shows together as much...
Hinata: Emu...
Emu: Oh, I should go brush my teeth...!
Emu: And I still need to do my best during practice tomorrow, so...! Night, Sis!
Hinata: ...
Shosuke's Voice: How's Emu doing...?
Hinata: She said she's fine...while crying...
Hinata: She tried her best to compose herself, but she probably still is in her bed right now...
Keisuke: I see...
Hinata: Do you have any ideas in mind...?
Hinata: I know it's not right for us to intervene since this is between her and her troupe. But...
Hinata: I want to see them smiling...
Keisuke: Me too...
Keisuke: Then, we'll...
